  "narrative": "<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Short impact summary</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">The scholarly work titled \"Working Through Colonial Collections,\" published by Leuven University Press in 2022, explores significant themes related to colonial collections, contributing to academic discourse within its field. Despite its current citation count of zero, the book has established a presence in commercial markets, as evidenced by listings on platforms like Amazon and Goodreads.</p>\n<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Full narrative</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">\"Working Through Colonial Collections\" represents a notable addition to the literature on colonial artifacts and their implications. Published by Leuven University Press in 2022, the book engages with critical themes in the discourse on colonialism and its enduring impacts on collections worldwide. Although the work has yet to receive citations, it has made its mark in commercial avenues, indicating potential academic interest despite a current absence of scholarly uptake.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">The book's relevance is underscored by its availability on prominent platforms such as Amazon and Goodreads, which reflect a commercial linkage evident in authors' efforts to reach broader audiences. This visibility might position the work favorably for future discourse and scholarship, suggesting that it could resonate with both academic and public audiences interested in colonial histories.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">While the current metrics do not reflect community discussions or high-fidelity mentions across social platforms, the book's thematic richness and potential applicability in related fields could encourage future engagement on various platforms. As the dialogue around colonial collections continues to evolve, the work's importance may warrant attention as scholars and practitioners seek to navigate and reassess the legacies of these collections.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">The lack of citations may not diminish the book's significance. Instead, it opens opportunities for the academic community to engage with its insights, encouraging future citations and discussions that could emerge as more scholars recognize its contributions. Ultimately, \"Working Through Colonial Collections\" stands as a foundational research output awaiting greater recognition and utilization in scholarly discussions related to colonialism and its artifacts.</p>",
